links.title: Qiagen Lifts 2020, 2021 Outlook On Covid-19 Test Demand; Shares Rise
links.description: Shares of Qiagen rose almost 3% in Tuesday's pre-market trading after the medical diagnostics company lifted its financial outlook for 2020 and 2021. Qiagen (QGEN ) said it now expects net sales for the fourth quarter to grow at least 32% at constant exchange rates (CER) year-on-year, compared to the previous guidance for an increase of 24% to 27%.

http://ooc.bz/l/65150

$QGEN
Qiagen N.V (QGEN), a medical testing company, on Tuesday raised its Q4 and full-year 2020 guidance for adjusted EPS and revenue and said it expected solid growth to continue in 2021.The company raised its Q4 adjusted EPS outlook to $0.64 to $0.65 from the prior guidance of $0.58 to $0.60. Net sales are expected to grow by at least 32% at constant exchange rates, up from the prior guidance of 24% to 27% growth.Full-year 2020 adjusted EPS is expected to be $2.13 to $2.14, up from the prior guidance of $2.07 to $2.09. Revenue for the year is expected to grow by 22% at constant exchange rates, higher than the previous forecast of a 20% growth.
